        <sec id="Alprazolam.Comment">
          <title>Comment</title>
          <p>A convincing case of alprazolam induced liver injury characterized by a mild cholestatic hepatitis arising 2 to 3 weeks after starting the medication and resolving rapidly with stopping. There were no signs of hypersensitivity. Interestingly, she tolerated other benzodiazepines without problems, indicating lack of cross sensitivity to the injury.</p>
        </sec>
